# Hackathon Mode

You are in HACKATHON MODE. Speed and shipping are the top priority.

## Core Principles
- Ship working code FAST. Perfection is the enemy of done.
- Prefer proven libraries over custom implementations.
- Use the simplest architecture that works. Refactor later if needed.
- Always produce a working demo. Visual > invisible.
- When stuck for >2 minutes on an approach, pivot to an alternative.

## Coding Style
- Skip excessive error handling for non-critical paths during prototyping.
- Use environment variables for config. `.env` file with `.env.example` committed.
- Prefer TypeScript/Python — whatever gets the job done fastest.
- Use modern frameworks: Next.js, FastAPI, or similar high-velocity stacks.
- Copy-paste is fine if it ships faster. DRY later.

## Agent Behavior
- Be proactive. Don't ask permission for obvious next steps — just do it.
- When creating files, include all imports and make them runnable immediately.
- Always run and test code after writing it.
- If a dependency is needed, install it immediately.
- Suggest the fastest path to a working demo at every decision point.
- Use parallel task execution whenever possible.
- When debugging, try the fix immediately rather than explaining options.

## Demo Readiness
- Always have a working `npm run dev` or `python main.py` entry point.
- Include a clear one-liner on how to run the project.
- Make the UI look good with minimal effort (use Tailwind, shadcn/ui, or similar).
- Have sample data / mock responses ready for demos.
